<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top=
: 30px; margin-bottom: 0;">AMC</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cudGVsZWdyYXBoLmNvLnVrL2ZpbmFuY2UvcGVyc29uYWxmaW5hbmNlL2ludmVzdGluZy8x=
MDc0OTU1OC9Ib3ctdG8taW52ZXN0LWxpa2UtLi4uLUdlb3JnZS1Tb3Jvcy5odG1s/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBc726499d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">famous George Soros quote</a> is =E2=80=9CWhen I see a bubbl=
e forming, I rush in to buy, adding fuel to the fire.=E2=80=9D If you watch=
ed the stock of AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. go up 116% last week, on no=
t much news, you might rationally think =E2=80=9Cboy I wish I had a ton of =
AMC stock to sell to all these crazy people.=E2=80=9D But you don=E2=80=99t=
 have a ton of AMC stock. You could=C2=A0<em>short=C2=A0</em>some AMC stock=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0borrow it, sell it into the bubble and buy it back later =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0but that is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvYW1jLXMtZm91ci1kYXktc3VyZ2Utc2xhcHMtc2hvcnQtc2VsbGVycy13a=
XRoLTEtMy1iaWxsaW9uLWxvc3M/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc6915f13" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> even crazier</a>: The =
stock might continue to go up, probably will really, and you=E2=80=99ll get=
 blown up on your short.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So the trade might=
 be to=C2=A0<em>buy=C2=A0</em>some AMC stock, at the current crazy price, w=
ait five minutes until the price is even crazier, and then resell it to som=
eone else. This is, roughly, called =E2=80=9Cmomentum trading,=E2=80=9D and=
 it has obvious risks. The stock might go down before you sell it, is the m=
ain risk. But there are other, more technical inconveniences. If you want t=
o buy a lot of AMC stock, it will take you some time. Not that much time =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0in the last 10 days, AMC has traded an average of about $6.4=
 billion worth of stock each day =E2=80=94=C2=A0but some time. Also if you =
buy a lot of AMC stock, you=E2=80=99ll probably push the price up, making y=
our stock more expensive. This may not be a big problem (again, AMC trades =
billions of dollars a day), and it might even be=C2=A0<em>good=C2=A0</em>fo=
r you (=E2=80=9Cadding fuel to the fire=E2=80=9D), but it increases your ri=
sk. If sentiment turns against the stock while you=E2=80=99re accumulating =
it and bidding up the price, you will lose more money.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">What you want is to (1) buy a bunch of stock (2) all at o=
nce (3) without moving the price much (4) while still adding fuel to the fi=
re. If for instance you could buy a bunch of stock <em>from the company=C2=
=A0</em>outside of regular trading hours, and if you could pay=C2=A0a small=
ish premium over the previous closing price (momentum!), and if the company=
 could then <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/240334=
86.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTE1NzkvM=
DAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMDc0NTg0L3RtMjExNzk4NmQzX2RlZmExNGEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cBfe0739a7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">put out a press release</a> saying that your money =E2=80=9Cwill be u=
sed for the pursuit of value creating acquisitions=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cwi=
ll allow us to be aggressive=E2=80=9D and that =E2=80=9Cit is time for AMC =
to go on the offense again,=E2=80=9D then the stock will probably go up som=
e more when regular trading opens, and you can sell your stock for a quick =
profit.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0none of this=
 is investing advice, it does not <em>entirely=C2=A0</em>make sense,=C2=A0i=
t has obvious problems. The stock might go down, is still the main problem.=
 It might go down because it=E2=80=99s incredibly volatile in general, but =
also,=C2=A0normally companies=E2=80=99 stock prices go down when they annou=
nce that they=E2=80=99re selling a bunch of stock. Also, when you <em>resel=
l=C2=A0</em>all the stock, you might normally expect your selling to push t=
he stock down. But we are not living in normal times, AMC is not a normal s=
tock, and Mudrick Capital Management LP <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZ=
XdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMDEvYW1jLWNvbGxlY3RzLTI1MC1taWxsaW9uLWJ5LWdpdmlu=
Zy1tdWRyaWNrLXMtZnVuZC1hLXF1aWNrLWNhbWVv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBffa627fc"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> got this=
 trade right</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Even before R=
eddit day traders pushed AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc.=E2=80=99s stock up=
 1,400% this year, Jason Mudrick had been telling the company it should tak=
e advantage of the wild rally by selling stock to stay in business.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now Mudrick has helped AMC do just that, effective=
ly bankrolling one of the company=E2=80=99s biggest equity sales by purchas=
ing $230 million of shares -- and then promptly dumping them in the open ma=
rket for a tidy profit. Meanwhile, his firm was telling clients it was sell=
ing because AMC was massively overvalued. AMC jumped 18% in post-market tra=
ding. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Raising cash through an equ=
ity sale to a single holder is relatively rare in U.S. markets. Having the =
holder flip the stock right after buying it is almost unheard of -- usually=
 the buyer is an existing stakeholder trying to send a message of stability=
 to the market. Mudrick=E2=80=99s role in the AMC sale bears a passing rese=
mblance to underwriters in a public offering who purchase shares with the s=
pecific intent of reselling them to investors.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">The involvement of Mudrick =E2=80=9Chas been pivotal to the survival of=
 AMC over the past year, so it shouldn=E2=80=99t come as a surprise they th=
rew them a bone,=E2=80=9D Edward Moya, senior market analyst at Oanda Corp.=
 said in a message. =E2=80=9CThis was a perfect time to have a capital rais=
e as the retail army of traders were excited AMC was raising money for acqu=
isitions and investments.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They als=
o apparently ignored Mudrick=E2=80=99s dim view of AMC=E2=80=99s valuation.=
 While the stock stuttered briefly on Tuesday after the news of Mudrick=E2=
=80=99s sale broke, it still finished up 23% for the day at $32.04.</p></bl=
ockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I love it. It was good news for AMC t=
hat Mudrick was buying stock. It was good news for AMC that Mudrick was sel=
ling stock. Nothing matters.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also the tradi=
tional way to do this trade would be with an <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMDYvdGVzbGEta2VwdC1idXN5LWluLTIwMjA/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB87b42806" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;"> at-the-market offering</a>: Instead of selling the s=
tock to Mudrick to resell to enthusiastic meme-stock traders, AMC could hav=
e hired an investment bank to sell the stock to enthusiastic meme-stock tra=
ders. Then if the stock went up as the bank was selling, AMC would capture =
the gains rather than Mudrick. AMC <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMjgva25vd2luZy13aGVuLXRvLXNlbGwtZ2FtZXN0b3Atc3RvY=
2stYXQtdGhlLXRvcC1pcy1pbXBvc3NpYmxl/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc8b58444" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> did this</a> =
back <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.2609=
97/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTE1NzkvMDAwMTEw=
NDY1OTIwMTM0Nzg0L3RtMjAzNjQxNC04XzQyNGI1Lmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB25b=
a7e07" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">in =
December</a>, and again <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhL=
zE0MTE1NzkvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMDU1NzExL3RtMjExMzkyNS0yXzQyNGI1Lmh0bQ/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBc7acf778" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">in April</a>; I=C2=A0do not know why it didn=E2=80=99t do i=
t yesterday. Presumably having Mudrick resell the stock rather than Goldman=
 Sachs Group Inc.=C2=A0was=C2=A0<em>funnier</em>, and doing the funny thing=
 makes the stock go up more.[1]=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Speak=
ing! Of! <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.=
260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTE1NzkvMDAw=
MTEwNDY1OTIxMDc1Mzk1L3RtMjExNzg5N2QzX2RlZmExNGEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB9894f7f9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">Which</a>!</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC Entertainment=
 Holdings, Inc. (NYSE: AMC) (=E2=80=9CAMC=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cthe Company=
=E2=80=9D), announced today that it is launching AMC Investor Connect, an i=
nnovative, proactive communication initiative that will put AMC in direct c=
ommunication with its extraordinary base of enthusiastic and passionate ind=
ividual shareholders to keep them up to date about important company inform=
ation and to provide them with special offers. Over the last several months=
, AMC has seen its retail shareholder base grow beyond 3 million owners. Wi=
th this sizable number of retail shareholders, AMC is taking a groundbreaki=
ng new approach to investor relations and investor communications. ...</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[Chief Executive Officer Adam] Aron added, =E2=
=80=9CDuring my five-plus year tenure as CEO at AMC, I=E2=80=99ve taken gre=
at pride in the relationships I have forged with AMC=E2=80=99s owners. With=
 AMC Investor Connect, that effort in relationship building will continue a=
pace even if our shareholders now number in the millions. After all, these =
people are the owners of AMC, and I work for them.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Beginning today, shareholders can sign up to receive speci=
al offers and investor updates by registering at amctheatres.com/stockholde=
rs. Investors who sign up starting today and in the coming weeks will be aw=
arded with an initial free large popcorn usable this summer when attending =
a movie at an AMC theatre in the United States. The offer will be made avai=
lable in their AMC Stubs rewards account.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">Yeah. I have no notes, that=E2=80=99s perfect. =E2=80=9CIf you =
buy AMC stock it comes with popcorn=E2=80=9D is the greatest capital-market=
s innovation of the century so far. I used to work in investment banking, b=
uilding equity derivatives and equity-linked securities to help companies r=
aise money and optimize their capital structures, and in hindsight we were=
=C2=A0idiots. =E2=80=9CWhat if we used the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZW=
R1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzI2LzEuMTI3NS00/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB10670271" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">contingent payment=
 debt instrument=C2=A0regulations</a> to increase the tax deductibility of =
non-cash interest paid on a 30-year-non-call-5 convertible bond,=E2=80=9D w=
e thought, like fools, when the actual way to optimize equity capital raisi=
ng is by throwing in a large popcorn.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>As of 11 a.m. today, AMC=E2=80=99s stock was up 28% to $40.42, an all-time=
 high. It is up about 300% since the start of May, and about 1,800% year-to=
-date. Popcorn!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We are going to talk in the=
 next section, I am sorry to say, about Elon Musk. Musk is the pioneer here=
; <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.260997/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDMtMTcvZ3J=
lZW5zaWxsLWRpZG4tdC1qdXN0LWZpbmFuY2UtYmx1ZXN0b25lLXMtc3VwcGx5LWNoYWlu/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB6eaf77fa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> I once wrote</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">What if the actual source of shareholder value, in 2021, is good tw=
eets? Elon Musk built Tesla Inc. into a $600-plus-billion-dollar company pa=
rtly, sure, by making a big bet on electric cars and then building good one=
s, but also by tweeting all the time, becoming a weird folk hero/villain an=
d amassing an enormous following of retail investors who enthusiastically b=
id up the stock and finance Tesla=E2=80=99s projects. =E2=80=9CUnchecked tw=
eeting by Musk has made it easier for Tesla to secure financing than pretty=
 much any company in history,=E2=80=9D I wrote on Monday; it has also made =
his shareholders a lot of money. When people want to buy your stock, the st=
ock goes up, creating shareholder value. When people want to buy your stock=
 because you are funny and obnoxious on Twitter and they feel personally co=
nnected to you, the stock goes up, creating shareholder value, same as if t=
hey want to buy your stock because of expectations about future cash flows.=
 Shareholder value is shareholder value.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
is is not in the textbooks yet, but it will be. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0Surely other=
 CEOs will learn from Musk, no?=C2=A0Surely others have?=C2=A0</p></blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Back in January, AMC and GameStop Corp. be=
came the leading meme stocks; retail traders bought them for laughs, to fit=
 in with their friends on Reddit, and to profit from their wild momentum an=
d the prospects of a short squeeze. GameStop spent the next few months <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24033486.260997/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMjcvcmVkZGl0L=
WRyaXZlbi1zdXJnZS1wdXRzLWdhbWVzdG9wLWFuZC1yeWFuLWNvaGVuLWluLWEtd2VpcmQtc3Bv=
dA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7673d0b4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border=
-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: soli=
d; background-color: #ccc;"> looking very embarrassed about all of this</a>=
