didn=E2=80=99t require authorization, according to the SEC=E2=80=99s corres=
pondence. When the SEC sought records related to the tweet, Tesla said ther=
e were none, the agency wrote in a May 8, 2020, letter to Tesla. Mr. Musk=
=E2=80=99s tweet addressed the company=E2=80=99s financial condition, a top=
ic subject to the policy, the SEC wrote.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
=E2=80=9CIn the face of Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s repeated refusals to submit his =
covered written communications on Twitter to Tesla for pre-approval, we are=
 very concerned by Tesla=E2=80=99s repeated determinations that there have =
been no policy violations because of purported carve-outs,=E2=80=9D the SEC=
 wrote in that letter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tesla=E2=80=99s outs=
ide counsel responded later that month that tweeting about Tesla=E2=80=99s =
