 a letter separately obtained by the Journal. The lawyers said regulators h=
ad tried to =E2=80=9Charass Tesla and silence Mr. Musk=E2=80=9D with invest=
igations that =E2=80=9Coverlapped endlessly.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s it, though, just a strongly worded l=
etter. I have to say, I think I had the better of this argument. Musk tweet=
ed something=C2=A0arguably material about Tesla, and the SEC sent Tesla a t=
hundering letter about how egregiously it had violated its settlement, and =
Tesla sent back a letter saying like =E2=80=9Cnyah nyah nyah what are you g=
onna do about it,=E2=80=9D and the answer was nothing.=C2=A0Better to do no=
thing to begin with! If I were the senior SEC official in charge of Tesla, =
and I read Elon Musk=E2=80=99s tweet saying that the stock price was too hi=
gh, I=E2=80=99d send Tesla a letter being like =E2=80=9Clol good one, ya sc=
